    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim the green stalk[s] off your <strong>aubergine[s]</strong> and discard, then chop into small bite-sized cubes</p><p>Heat a pot (with a matching lid) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped aubergine </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-lentil-stew/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel your <strong>garlic </strong>and chop it in half, reserve one piece per person for later</p><p>Finely grate the <strong>remaining garlic halves</strong></p><p>Rinse your<strong> red lentils</strong> in a sieve under <strong>cold running water</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-lentil-stew/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the aubergine is lightly browned, reduce the heat to medium and tear your <strong>'Nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) into the pot</p><p>Add the <strong>grated garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>dried thyme </strong>with your<strong> tomato paste</strong>,<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong>,<strong> rinsed red lentils </strong>and<strong> chicken stock mix</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-lentil-stew/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add 450ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[675ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [900ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook, covered, for 15-20 min or until the lentils are tender, stirring occasionally \u2013 this is your<strong> 'Nduja & aubergine lentil stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-lentil-stew/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-lentil-stew/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the 'Nduja aubergine & lentil stew<strong> </strong>is ready, stir through <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a small pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Set aside, with the lid on, for 2-3 min for the flavours to develop \u2013 this is your <strong>one pot</strong> <strong>spicy 'Nduja & aubergine lentil stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-lentil-stew/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Place the <strong>halved ciabatta[s] </strong>in the<strong> toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until toasted</p><p>Once the ciabatta is toasted, rub the sliced-side of the <strong>reserved</strong> <strong>garlic </strong>over it (not a fan of raw garlic? Only use a little!)</p><p>Spread a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over the toasted ciabatta \u2013 this is your <strong>garlicky toast</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/one-pot-spicy-nduja-and-aubergine-lentil-stew/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Tear your <strong>basil</strong> over the <strong>one pot</strong> <strong>spicy 'Nduja & aubergine lentil stew </strong>and top with the<strong> remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Serve with the <strong>garlicky toast </strong>to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
